  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves hiding the origins of illegally obtained money through a series of transactions designed to make the funds appear legal. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically include:\n\n1. Core elements:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming \"dirty\" money into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Disguising the true ownership or origin of money\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Deliberately hiding proceeds from criminal activities\n- Engaging in financial transactions to obscure illegal origins\n- Attempting to make illegally obtained funds appear legal\n\n3. Typical prohibited actions:\n- Transferring funds through complex financial systems\n- Structuring transactions to avoid reporting requirements\n- Investing criminal proceeds in legitimate businesses\n- Creating false documentation about fund sources\n\n4. Key jurisdictional variations:\n- United States: Defined under Title 18 U.S. Code Section 1956\n- European Union: Follows anti-money laundering directives\n- International standards set by Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n\nThese are general legal descriptions. Specific definitions can vary, so consulting local legal authorities is recommended for precise details.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
